message:
Some adjustments.
(As suggested by @alexander255)

title: PhoneNumberUtils.formatNumberToE164 returns (null), if it doesn't know what to…
message: PhoneNumberUtils.formatNumberToE164 returns (null), if it doesn't know what to do. We need to catch that.

title: Possible Bugfix: uri encode phone number for sms: ACTION_SENDTO call (as for
message:
Possible Bugfix: uri encode phone number for sms: ACTION_SENDTO call (as for
ACTION_CALL calls).

Minor fixes:
 * for API >= LOLLIPOP: call formatNumber for E164 formatted number (adds
   spaces, nicer to look at).
 * prefix entry parsing was writing log warnings for entries not matching the
   current country (should have been: only for entries with field count != 4).

title: Cleanup
message:
Cleanup
 * switched to production (use our phone number normalization as backup only)
 * removed libphonenumber submodule & added hint to generate-mobile-phone-regex.py
 * pattern for ignored characters in phonenumbers is compiled once and reused.

title: Issue 480 (continued)
message:
Issue 480 (continued)
 * Since we don't expect the phone to change its country, store country iso code in PhoneNormalizer (was a parameter).
 * Determine country iso code by using sim and network country, locale just as fallback.
 * international prefix is a regex pattern, use accordingly.
 * Also remove (ignore) slashes in contact phone numbers.

title: Incorporated new prefix csv data, built by @alexander255.
message:
Incorporated new prefix csv data, built by @alexander255.
 * PhoneNormalizer now uses PhoneNumberUtils.formatNumberToE164 if available.
 * otherwise it'll use our own mechanism based on libphonenumber data & suggestions by @alexander255.
 * libphonenumber submodule updated to latest version.
 * generate-mobile-phone-regex.py now returns a sorted list of tuples (more stable output .. order of dict items is semi-random).

title: Improve performance by changing the way nicknames are loaded

Improve performance by changing the way nicknames are loaded

Instead of querying the database for every single nickname, a single
query retrieves them all. The nicknames are then added as members of the
contacts in the existing contactMap.

message:
Menu item to exclude apps on long press on the app list.
Option to reset the excluded list in KISS settings.

All excluded apps are stored in one "semicolon separated" string in the shared preferences.
(List of strings not available on older apis).
The default value of the string is the KISS package
While loading, all apps that are inside this list are not returned
